---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead 
		title={`Google Pixel 7a with GrapheneOS | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
		description="Privacy-focused, security-hardened mobile platform with GrapheneOS pre-installed on Google Pixel 7a hardware. Hardware security features and open-source transparency."
	/>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="#main-content" class="skip-to-main">Skip to main content</a>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content">
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="hero-title-group">
					<img src="/images/graphenelogo.png" alt="GrapheneOS Logo" class="hero-logo" />
					<h1>Google Pixel 7a with GrapheneOS</h1>
				</div>
				<p class="tagline">Hardened Mobile Security Platform</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="card">
					<div class="product-header">
						<span class="badge">Privacy-Focused Operating System</span>
					</div>
					<p class="product-intro">The Google Pixel 7a running GrapheneOS provides a privacy-focused, security-hardened mobile platform that doesn't compromise on usability. GrapheneOS is a non-profit open-source project focused on privacy and security research, offering enhanced exploit mitigations, privacy protections, and full Android app compatibility.</p>
					
					<div class="highlight-box">
						<h3>Pre-Installed Privacy Applications</h3>
						<p>Each device comes pre-configured with essential privacy and security applications: <strong>SimpleX Chat</strong> for private messaging, <strong>Tuta Mail</strong> for encrypted email, <strong>Aurora Store</strong> and <strong>F-Droid</strong> for app distribution, <strong>NetGuard</strong> for firewall protection, <strong>Tor Browser</strong>, <strong>IronFox</strong> browser, and <strong>Signal</strong> for secure communications.</p>
						<p><strong>Free Customization Service:</strong> We provide complimentary customization recommendations and implementation with each phone purchase, tailored to your specific privacy and security requirements.</p>
					</div>
					
					<h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
					
					<div class="specs-grid">
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Security-First Operating System</strong>
							<p>GrapheneOS is a privacy and security-focused mobile OS with full Android app compatibility. Developed as a non-profit open-source project, it undergoes continuous security research and includes substantial hardening beyond standard Android.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Hardware Security Features</strong>
							<p>Pixel 7a includes Google's Titan M2 dedicated security chip, verified boot chain with rollback protection, hardware-backed key storage, and secure element for cryptographic operations. The device supports full disk encryption with hardware acceleration.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Hardened System Architecture</strong>
							<p>Enhanced exploit mitigations including hardened memory allocator, hardened C library, compiler exploit mitigations, and extensive attack surface reduction. MAC randomization prevents network-level tracking and reduces fingerprinting vectors.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Privacy Protections</strong>
							<p>No Google Play Services by default, eliminating privileged system-level tracking. Network permission toggle per-app, storage scopes limiting filesystem access, contact scopes for granular permission control, and sensors permission preventing background sensor access.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>App Compatibility</strong>
							<p>Run standard Android apps in a hardened sandboxed environment. Optional sandboxed Google Play Services provides app compatibility without system integration or privileged access. Apps function normally without sacrificing privacy or security.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Pre-Configured & Ready</strong>
							<p>Devices are supplied with GrapheneOS professionally installed, pre-loaded with essential privacy applications (SimpleX, Tuta Mail, Aurora, F-Droid, NetGuard, Tor, IronFox, Signal), configured for optimal security settings, and ready for immediate deployment. Includes verified boot with user-controlled keys and OTA update support.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Hardware Specifications</strong>
							<p>Google Tensor G2 processor with Titan M2 security coprocessor. 8GB LPDDR5 RAM, 128GB storage. 6.1" OLED display (1080x2400, 90Hz). Dual rear cameras (64MP + 13MP ultrawide), 13MP front camera. IP67 dust and water resistance.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Verified Boot</strong>
							<p>Complete verified boot chain from hardware root of trust through operating system. User-controlled verified boot keys allow detection of unauthorized system modifications. Rollback protection prevents downgrade attacks to vulnerable firmware versions.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Network Privacy</strong>
							<p>Per-connection MAC randomization, no persistent hardware identifiers broadcast to networks. DNS over HTTPS by default. Optional always-on VPN enforcement and kill switch to prevent data leakage outside tunnel.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Permission Model</strong>
							<p>Extended Android permission system with additional controls. Network permission toggle per-app, sensors permission to block background access, storage scopes limiting filesystem access, and contact/storage scopes for granular data access control.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Open Source Transparency</strong>
							<p>Fully open-source operating system with transparent development process. Independent security audits, reproducible builds for verification, and active security research community. No hidden proprietary components or telemetry.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Update Support</strong>
							<p>Regular security updates delivered via over-the-air (OTA) updates. GrapheneOS provides extended support beyond standard Android EOL. Seamless A/B updates minimize downtime and provide rollback capability.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Device Availability</strong>
							<p>Google Pixel 7a currently in stock for immediate shipment. Custom orders available for Pixel 7a through Pixel 10 XL Pro models (1-3 business days processing). All devices professionally configured with GrapheneOS and privacy application suite.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<h2>Use Cases</h2>
					<div class="use-cases">
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Privacy-Conscious Professionals</h4>
							<p>Journalists, lawyers, activists, and researchers requiring confidential communications, secure document handling, and protection from network surveillance.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Enterprise Security</h4>
							<p>Organizations requiring mobile devices with hardened security posture, verifiable integrity, and reduced attack surface for accessing sensitive corporate resources.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Threat-Aware Individuals</h4>
							<p>Users facing elevated threat models requiring protection from sophisticated adversaries, exploitation attempts, and persistent surveillance capabilities.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Security Research</h4>
							<p>Security professionals and researchers requiring a transparent, auditable mobile platform for secure communications and development of privacy-preserving applications.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="availability-notice">
						<h3>Device Options & Availability</h3>
						<p><strong>In Stock:</strong> Google Pixel 7a available for immediate purchase and shipment.</p>
						<p><strong>Custom Orders:</strong> We can configure any Google Pixel device from the 7a through the Pixel 10 XL Pro with GrapheneOS upon request. Custom device orders are processed and shipped within 1-3 business days.</p>
						<p><strong>Free Customization:</strong> Every phone includes complimentary customization consultation where we assess your security requirements and implement tailored configurations, additional privacy applications, and security policies specific to your threat model.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="back-to-products">
					<a href="/products" class="btn secondary">‚Üê Back to Products</a>
					<a href="mailto:hello@hermetrix.nz" class="btn primary">Order This Product</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />

	<style>
		.hero {
			padding: var(--space-3xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.hero-title-group {
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}

		.hero-logo {
			height: 80px;
			width: auto;
		}

		.tagline {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			margin-top: var(--space-md);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		}

		.card {
			background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
		}

		.product-header {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
		}

		.badge {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
			background: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.1);
			border: 2px solid var(--accent-secondary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-size: 0.75rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.1em;
			box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.2);
		}

		.product-intro {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.8;
		}

		.card h2 {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			font-size: 1.875rem;
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.specs-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.spec-item {
			padding: var(--space-lg);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
			backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
			border: 2px solid var(--white);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.spec-item:hover {
			border-color: var(--accent-secondary);
			transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
			box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.3);
		}

		.spec-item strong {
			display: block;
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
			font-size: 1rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.spec-item p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.9375rem;
			line-height: 1.6;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		.use-cases {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			margin-top: var(--space-xl);
		}

		.use-case-item {
			padding: var(--space-lg);
			background: rgba(0, 204, 204, 0.05);
			border: 2px solid var(--accent-secondary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.use-case-item:hover {
			background: rgba(0, 204, 204, 0.1);
			transform: translateY(-2px);
		}

		.use-case-item h4 {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm) 0;
			font-size: 1.125rem;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.use-case-item p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.9375rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.6;
		}

		.highlight-box {
			padding: var(--space-xl);
			background: rgba(0, 204, 204, 0.08);
			border: 2px solid var(--accent-secondary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			margin: var(--space-2xl) 0;
			box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 204, 204, 0.1);
		}

		.highlight-box h3 {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
			font-weight: 900;
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.highlight-box p {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.7;
			font-size: 1rem;
		}

		.highlight-box p:last-child {
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		.highlight-box strong {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			font-weight: 700;
		}

		.availability-notice {
			padding: var(--space-xl);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
			border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-secondary);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 204, 204, 0.1);
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.availability-notice h3 {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
			font-weight: 900;
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.availability-notice p {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.7;
		}

		.availability-notice p:last-child {
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		.availability-notice strong {
			color: var(--accent-secondary);
			font-weight: 700;
		}

		.back-to-products {
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
			display: flex;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			justify-content: center;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}

		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.hero {
				padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
			}

			.hero-logo {
				height: 48px;
			}

			.specs-grid {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.use-cases {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.back-to-products {
				flex-direction: column;
			}

			.highlight-box,
			.availability-notice {
				padding: var(--space-lg);
			}
		}
	</style>
</body>
</html>
